    "茶叶滋味是茶叶化学组成部分含量和人的感官对它的综合反应。茶叶有甜、酸、苦、鲜、涩等多种滋味。鲜味主要成分是多种氨基酸，氨基酸鲜中带甜，有的鲜中带酸。涩的主要特质是多酚类化合物。甜味物质主要有部分氨基酸和可溶性糖。苦味物质主要有咖啡碱、花青素、茶叶皂素。酸味物质主要是多种有机酸。":"Tea taste results from its chemical composition interacting with human senses. It offers a spectrum of flavors: sweet, sour, bitter, fresh, and astringent. Umami is primarily driven by diverse amino acids, with some being both fresh and sweet, while others are fresh and sour. Astringency is chiefly attributed to polyphenolic compounds. Sweetness comes from amino acids and soluble sugars. Bitterness arises from caffeine, anthocyanins, and tea saponins. Sourness mainly stems from various organic acids.",

