    "茶的最早发现": "The earliest discovery of tea",
    "【茶的最早发现】陆羽《茶经》中说“茶之为饮，发乎神农氏”相传在公元前2700多年前的神农时代，神农为普济众生，常百草，采草药。有一天尝到一种草叶，使他口干舌燥，头晕目眩。于是背靠旁边的大树坐下休息，突然，一阵风过，传来一种清鲜香气，抬头望去树上绿叶葱茏。神农信手摘下一片放入只中咀嚼，味出苦，继而清香甘甜，食后更觉气味清香，舌底生津，精神爽朗，头晕目眩减轻，口干舌燥渐渐消失。神农遂名为“茶”，这便是茶的最早发现。": "[The earliest discovery of tea] Lu Yu's 'The Tea Sutra' said that 'tea is drinking, and it is about Shennong's family'. It was said that in the Shennong era more than 2700 years ago, Shennong was a Puji beings, and he often took grass and picked herbs.One day he tasted a kind of grass leaf that made him dry and dizzy.So he sat down and resting on the big tree next to him. Suddenly, a gust of wind passed, and a fresh aroma came, looking up at the green leaves on the tree.Shennongxin took a piece of chewing in his hand, and the taste was bitter, and then the fragrance was sweet and sweet.Shennong was named 'Tea', which was the earliest discovery of tea.'",
    "茶叶制作出现": "Tea production appears",
    "种植茶树，茶叶制作出现": "Tea tree, tea production appears",
    "第一次贡茶和史上最早茶叶史料": "The first tribute tea and earliest tea history in history",
    "史上第一次贡茶和史上最早茶叶史料。公元前1046年，武王伐纣。周武王伐纣后，巴国以茶与其它珍贵产品纳贡，这是最早史料记载的史上第一次贡茶。同时，记载里巴国就有人工栽培茶树的茶园了。距今已3067年。": "The first tribute tea in history and the earliest tea historical materials in history.In 1046 BC, the King of Wu fell.After the king of Zhou Wu fell out, Pakistani made a tribute with tea and other precious products. This is the first time in history of historical records.At the same time, it is recorded that the tea gardens of artificially cultivated tea trees are recorded.It has been 3067 years ago.",
    "闻于鲁周公": "Wen Yu Lu Zhougong",
    "【闻于鲁周公】《茶经》记载，“茶之为饮，发乎神农氏，闻于鲁周公”说明周代既有茶出现": "[Wen Yu Zhou Gong] 'Tea Sutra' records, 'Tea is drinking, it is about Shennong's family, smelling in Lu Zhougong' shows that the existing tea in the Zhou Dynasty appeared",
    "茶入中原": "Tea enter Central Plains",
    "【茶入中原】春秋时代，茶叶用作祭品和蔬菜。随着大规模战争和人口迁徙，茶由巴蜀传入中原": "[Tea enters the Central Plains] In the Spring and Autumn Period, tea is used as a sacrifice and vegetables.With the migration of large -scale wars and population, tea was introduced from Bashu into the Central Plains",
    "茶叶首次被文字记载": "Tea is recorded for the first time by text",
    "茶叶首次被文字记载": "Tea is recorded for the first time by text",
    "汉阳陵出土最早遗存茶叶实物": "The earliest relics of tea unearthed from Hanyang Mausoleum",
    "汉阳陵出土最早遗存茶叶实物，距今2150年之久。这是实证的汉代皇室御用茶叶，更是确证汉代皇室饮用茶芽。这意味着饮茶方式、制茶方式、储存方式的重要变革，对后世制茶饮茶有着极为深远的影响。": "The earliest relics of tea unearthed in Hanyang Mausoleum, which is 2150 years old.This is an empirical Han Dynasty royal royal tea, and it is also confirmed that the Han Dynasty royal family drinking tea buds.This means that the important changes in tea drinking, tea making, and storage methods have a profound impact on later tea -making tea drinking.",
    "史上最早的茶叶向外传播": "The earliest tea in history spread outward",
    "史上最早的茶叶向外传播。公元前119年，汉代张骞第二次出使中西亚，携带有茶叶。公元前108年，汉武帝征服朝鲜，将茶叶传入日本福冈。这是最早史料记载的茶叶向外传播行为，距今已2220年。": "The earliest tea in history spread outward.In 119 BC, Zhang Jian, a Han Dynasty, made a secondary envoy in Central and Western Asia and carried tea.In 108 BC, Emperor Hanwu conquered North Korea and introduced tea into Fukuoka, Japan.This is the earliest historical record of tea. It has been 2220 years ago.",
    "汉代武都茶叶市场": "Han Dynasty Wudu Tea Market",
    "汉代武都茶叶市场：史上第一家茶叶交易市场。公元前59年，西汉蜀郡王褒与杨惠签署《僮约》购买仆人，并在契约中进行了超过一百项的工作约定。其中有两处涉及到茶：烹荼尽具、武都买荼。武都，在四川眉山地区，这是最早记载的史上第一家茶叶交易市场。距今已2079年。": "Wu Du Tea Market in the Han Dynasty: The first tea trading market in history.In 59 BC, Wang Yi and Yang Hui of Shu County in the Western Han Dynasty signed the 'Children's Treaty' to buy a servant and conducted more than 100 work agreement in the contract.Two of them involved tea: the cooking is full, and the martial arts buy.Wudu, in the Meishan area of Sichuan, is the first tea trading market in history.It has been 2079.",
    "蜀之贡品": "Shutan Tribute",
    "【蜀之贡品】武王伐纣以后，巴蜀为封国，文献记载就有茶叶为贡品的记载": "[The tribute of Shu Zhi] After the king of Wu, Bashu was the kingdom, and the literature records had the record of tea as a tribute.",
    "茶风初成": "Tea wind",
