    "【来喝下午茶吧】自凯瑟琳公主嫁往英国，茶逐渐在英国贵妇阶层中形成以红茶为主的饮下午茶风气": "[Come to drink afternoon tea bar] Since Princess Catherine marrys to the UK, tea has gradually formed in the British lady class.",
    "茶在国外的广泛推广": "The extensive promotion of tea abroad",
    "零售店店主家庭的预算中，每周要花3先令给全家人买面包，花4先令买茶叶和糖。正如一位评论家1757年所言，无论男女老少，身体健壮的还是文弱的，富有的还是穷人、乞丐，当他们口渴的时候会喝这种饮料，不渴的时候还会喝这种饮料。": "In the budget of the owner's family of the retail store, spend 3 orders to buy bread for the whole family per week, and buy tea and sugar.As a critic said in 1757, regardless of whether men, women, and children, the body is strong or weak.Essence",
    "零售茶叶业务的扩展": "Expansion of retail tea business",
    "到18世纪下半叶，零售茶叶的业务逐渐从药店转到食品杂货店，反映了茶从药品到饮料的角色转变，真正成为广大社会下层平民的日常饮料。": "By the second half of the 18th century, the business of retail tea has gradually moved from pharmacies to food grocery stores, reflecting the change of tea from drugs to drinks, and truly becomes a daily drink for the lower levels of civilians in the society.",
    "饮茶有害论": "Drinking tea is harmful",
    "饮茶有害论。早在1722年，当时饮茶还不太普遍的时候，有人就通过给动物喝茶的方法来测试茶叶的副作用。": "Drinking tea is harmful.As early as 1722, when drinking tea was not very common, some people tested the side effects of tea by drinking tea for animals.",
    "波士顿倾茶事件": "Boston Tea incident",
    "波士顿倾茶事件，由殖民地的民间反抗组织“自由之子”领导并行动，反对英国政府在殖民地征税并借此控制殖民地政府，以及反对英国东印度公司利用法案垄断北美的茶叶进口贸易，最终导致1775年美国革命战争爆发。": "The Boston tea incident was led by the colonial folk resistance organization 'Son of Freedom' and acted to oppose the British government's taxation in the colonies and use it to control the colonial government, as well as against the use of the British East Indian company to monopolize the import trade in North America.The American Revolutionary War broke out in 1775.",
    "茶进入美国": "Tea enters the United States",
    "随着英国人移民北美，茶因此进入美国，并在公元（1775年）见证了因「茶叶条款」引发的美国独立战争事件。": "As the British immigrated to North America, tea entered the United States, and witnessed the American independence war incident caused by the 'tea clause' in AD (1775).",
    "《抵代税法》": "'Tax Law'",
    "茶叶《抵代税法》（Commuta⁃tionAct）通过，茶叶关税率由之前的119%，下降到12.5%。茶叶关税的大幅降低，从长远看符合政府的财政利益，政府每年从关税和消费税中至少获利数十万镑。": "Tea 'Commuta⁃TionAct' passed, and the tea tax closing rate dropped from 119%before to 12.5%.The significant reduction of tea tariffs has complied with the government's fiscal interests in the long run.",
    "饮茶习俗已经随处可见": "The custom of drinking tea has been seen everywhere",
    "英国从宫殿到茅舍，饮茶习俗已经随处可见，反映了茶已经成为廉价大众消费饮品。": "From the palace to the cottage, the custom of drinking tea has been seen everywhere, reflecting that tea has become a cheap mass consumer drink.",
    "前所未有的繁荣": "Unprecedented prosperity",
    "【前所未有的繁荣】武夷茶出口量较前50年有明显增长，1792年达到1835万公斤，是上世纪末平均出口量的815倍": "[Unprecedented prosperity] Wuyi tea exports increased significantly from the previous 50 years. In 1792, it reached 18.35 million kilograms, which was 815 times the average export volume at the end of the last century.",
    "印度阿萨姆茶叶产地。": "The place of tea from Assam, India.",
